      "content": "The Apex Phone Pro and Zenith X are two high-end smartphones that boast impressive specs, but which one reigns supreme? \n\nThe Apex Phone Pro features a 6.7\" OLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate, providing a smooth visual experience. In contrast, the Zenith X boasts a slightly larger 6.8\" AMOLED screen with a 144Hz refresh rate, offering even more fluid visuals. \n\nBoth phones are powered by top-of-the-line processors - the Apex Phone Pro's Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 and the Zenith X's Dimensity 9300. The Apex Phone Pro comes with 12GB of RAM, while the Zenith X offers 16GB of RAM, making it a better choice for heavy users. \n\nIn terms of camera capabilities, both phones feature a 50MP main camera, but the Apex Phone Pro has a slightly better low-light performance. \n\nThe battery life of the two phones is also comparable, with the Apex Phone Pro's 4500mAh battery and the Zenith X's 5000mAh battery providing all-day use. \n\nBoth phones have an IP68 rating, ensuring they can withstand the elements. \n\nOverall, while both phones offer impressive specs,",
